# Frontend (Vite + React + MUI)

## Folder structure

```
frontend/src/
  pages/       # route screens (e.g. TodosPage)
  components/  # reusable UI (TodoItem, TodoForm, AppLoader, EmptyState)
  api/         # Axios client + endpoint functions
  hooks/       # data/UI hooks (useTodos, useUndoSnackbar)
  utils/       # pure helpers — use // for complex logic
  constants/   # API URLs, limits (MAX_TASKS_PER_CATEGORY = 5)
  types/       # TS interfaces matching backend DTOs
```

## Stack

- React functional components + TypeScript
- MUI for layout, forms, Snackbar, CircularProgress, empty/error states
- React Hook Form for the create-todo form
- Axios only in `api/` — hooks/components call api modules, never raw axios in JSX
- React Testing Library + Vitest for tests

## Patterns

```tsx
// ✅ pages compose only
const { todos, isLoading, error } = useTodos(categoryFilter);

// ✅ api/todosApi.ts — all HTTP here
export const createTodo = (data: CreateTodoDto) => api.post('/todos', data);
```

- Pages compose components and hooks; no fetch logic or validation rules in pages
- Shared wrappers (`LoadingOverlay`, `ErrorMessage`) live in `components/`
- Undo snackbar: centralize timer/restore in `useUndoSnackbar`, do not duplicate in handlers
- Map backend errors to user messages via a helper in `utils/` or `api/`
